The tears of Paulus are supposed to find their way into the lower world. All acts done to or in connection with the dead are con- cieved, not only as known, but as actually done, in the world below.

8. A good example of the confusion between the real and the imaginary already noticed: ¹ The lurid gateway looks up the grassy pyres.' The meaning is, ‘The dark door is shut upon the occupant of the grassy grave! There is no need to change herbosos into um- brosos. The pyre was built with turs, or upon it: no word would more truly and simply characterise the surroundings of the grave. Pinder's explanation that herbosos strengthens the notion os the grave as a closed place seems sancisul.
